The paper deals with the design of a Bit-Interleaved Coded Modulation (BICM) transceiver, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. However, the most relevant sub-category is likely to be Information Theory (cs.IT), as the paper deals with the optimization of a communication system in the presence of noise and fading. Other relevant sub-categories include Communications (cs.COMM), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Multimedia (cs.MM), as the paper also deals with the design of modulation schemes, multiplexing, and interleaving techniques, which are important components of communication systems, as well as the analysis of performance metrics such as bit error rate (BER).
